               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430918-name-714" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430918-name-714" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430918-name-714" type="surname" value="WOOD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430918-name-714" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>CHARLES WOOD</persName>
                  </hi>. I am errand-boy to Mr. Joseph Waite. On the 11th of Sept., a little before eight o'clock at night, I was sitting behind the desk, and saw the prisoner at the door, moving the boots about, which bung inside the shop—he ran off, and I ran after him, calling "Stop thief"—I kept close behind him to Brewer-street till he was stopped—these are my master's boots.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430918-name-715" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430918-name-715" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430918-name-715" type="surname" value="PUTTUX"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430918-name-715" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>MARY PUTTUX</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Eaton-lane, Pimlico. A little after eight o'clock I saw the prisoner running down Brewer-street—he threw one boot away—I took it up and gave it to my husband, who gave it to the policeman—this is the boot—the ticket is on it now.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430918-name-716" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430918-name-716" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430918-name-716" type="surname" value="LAMBERT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430918-name-716" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>ROBERT LAMBERT</persName>
                  </hi>. I found this other boot in a garden in Warwick-row—a man going along Brewer-street could have thrown it there—it is just across the street.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I was running the way the mob was; I knew no more than the others did.</p>
